# Custom Code Style Guide

My preferred code style to facilitate consistent coding, code refactoring and improve readability.

## General Rules

- use spaces rather than tabs

## GLSL Naming Conventions

```GLSL
#version 440

// whenever possible, explicitly specify locations (indices) for attributes
layout(location = 1) in vec4 position;
layout(location = 2) in vec4 color;

// user-defined variables to be shared between shader stages, prefixed by _
flat in vec4 _color;
smooth out vec4 _color;

// use snake_case for normal variables
const float loop_time = 2.0f;
float time_scale = 3.141592653f * 2.0f / loop_time;

// use PascalCase for user-defined output to be consumed by the current stage
layout(location = 0) out vec4 Color;

// use PascalCase for function names
vec4 FooBar() { }
```
